{"label":"Agile","id":"agile","list":[{"label":"Multiple Choice Question","type":"mcq","id":"test","commonData":{"title":"Multiple Choice Question","allowFrac":false},"data":[{"questions":[{"qText":"Agile is primarily a methodology for","options":"software development\nhardware design\nnetwork configuration\ndatabase backup"},{"qText":"Which of the following is a key Agile framework?","options":"scrum\nwaterfall\nspiral\nv-model"},{"qText":"Agile emphasizes","options":"iterative development\nsequential development\nbig design upfront\ndelayed testing"},{"qText":"In Agile, requirements and solutions evolve through","options":"collaboration\ndocumentation\nstrict planning\ncontract negotiation"},{"qText":"Which role in Scrum is responsible for maximizing product value?","options":"product owner\nscrum master\ndeveloper\nstakeholder"}]},{"questions":[{"qText":"The Scrum Master is mainly responsible for","options":"facilitating the process\ndefining requirements\nwriting code\napproving budgets"},{"qText":"Which Agile ceremony is held daily to discuss progress and blockers?","options":"daily stand-up\nsprint review\nretrospective\nplanning poker"},{"qText":"The time-boxed iteration in Scrum is called a","options":"sprint\nphase\nmilestone\ncycle"},{"qText":"Which artifact in Scrum lists the work that needs to be done?","options":"product backlog\nproject charter\ntest plan\ngantt chart"},{"qText":"A sprint retrospective focuses on","options":"improving team processes\nreviewing the product\nassigning tasks\nwriting documentation"}]},{"questions":[{"qText":"Which Agile practice is used to estimate story points?","options":"planning poker\ngantt charting\nPERT analysis\nwaterfall estimation"},{"qText":"Agile promotes working software as a measure of","options":"progress\ncost\neffort\nsize"},{"qText":"Which Agile principle encourages welcoming changes even late in development?","options":"responding to change\ncontract negotiation\nheavy documentation\nstrict planning"},{"qText":"In Agile, customer collaboration is valued more than","options":"contract negotiation\nprototyping\ntesting\ndeployment"},{"qText":"Continuous integration in Agile helps in","options":"detecting issues early\navoiding team meetings\ndelaying testing\neliminating coding standards"}]}]},{"label":"Drag and Drop","id":"dragdrop","type":"matchByDragDrop","data":{"fontSize":"1.3rem","dashWidth":80,"text":"Short meeting where the team shares progress and blockers : *Daily Stand-up*\nA prioritized list of features, enhancements, and fixes : *Product Backlog*\nAgile framework with roles, events, and artifacts : *Scrum* \nA time-boxed iteration, usually 1–4 weeks : *Sprint*\nA description of a feature from the end-user's perspective : *User Story*\nEnsures the team follows Agile practices and removes obstacles : *Scrum Master*\nThe person responsible for defining and prioritizing product needs : *Product Owner*\nA potentially shippable piece of software delivered at the end of a sprint  : *Increment*"}},{"type":"classifySentence","label":"True or False","id":"true-false","data":{"title":"True or False","types":[{"name":"True","text":"Agile focuses on iterative and incremental development.\nScrum is one of the popular frameworks of Agile.\nIn Agile, working software is considered the primary measure of progress.\nA daily stand-up is a short meeting held to track progress and blockers.\nA sprint retrospective is used to improve team processes."},{"name":"False","text":"Agile requires completing all requirements before any development starts.\nIn Agile, customer collaboration is less important than contract negotiation.\nScrum defines the project manager role as essential.\nTesting is done only after the entire product is developed in Agile.\nAgile discourages changes once development has started."}]}},{"id":"fillup","label":"Fill in the blanks","type":"fillup","data":{"title":"Fill in the blanks","fontSize":"1.4rem","text":"Agile focuses on *iterative (sequential, waterfall)* development.\nScrum is a popular *framework (language, database)* used in Agile.\nIn Agile, *working software (documents, contracts)* is the primary measure of progress.\nA time-boxed iteration in Scrum is called a *sprint (phase, milestone)*.\nThe person responsible for maximizing product value is the *product owner (scrum master, developer)*.\nThe daily team meeting in Scrum is called a *stand-up (retrospective, review)*.\nA list of all work items for a product is called the *product backlog (test plan, gantt chart)*.\nThe *scrum master (project manager, architect)* facilitates the Scrum process and removes blockers.\nThe meeting held at the end of a sprint to improve processes is a *retrospective (demo, estimation)*.\nAgile values customer *collaboration (negotiation, documentation)* over contract negotiation."}}]}